{"questionId":"27970237","questionHtml":"<p>Solve the equation <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>g</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></math>. Give your answer in the form <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>b</mi></math>,&nbsp;where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℚ</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>3</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>5</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mn>5</mn></math></p>\n<p>attempt to collect together terms in <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math> or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>f</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">e</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>f</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mfenced><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>5</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for each correct term given in exact form.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"27970237","referenceCode":"24M.2.SL.TZ1.7d","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Solve the equation fx=gx. Give your answer in the form x=a+ln b, where a, b ∈ℚ.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"d","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.10—Solving equations graphically and analytically","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.7—Laws of exponents and logs"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}